# दोष and stuck terms — the two faces of "failure" in Sūtra.
# Run with:  sutra run examples/dosha.sutra

# 1. An error-as-value: taking the head of an empty list yields a दोष term,
#    which is ordinary data you can inspect or recover from.
प्रयोग शीर्ष(रिक्त)।

# 2. Recovering from a दोष: यदि लets us choose a default. Here we ask whether
#    a list is empty first and supply ० as a fallback head.
सूत्र सुरक्षितशीर्ष(रिक्त) -> ०।
सूत्र सुरक्षितशीर्ष(युग्म(?क, ?श)) -> ?क।
प्रयोग सुरक्षितशीर्ष(रिक्त)।

# 3. A stuck term: there is no rule for the head of a number, so the term simply
#    does not reduce. The normal form *is* the (irreducible) term — Sūtra has no
#    exceptions, only terms that stop rewriting.
प्रयोग शीर्ष(५)।
